This paper discusses the bias of search engines and their impact on the traffic of users, which is a topic related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and social networks (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses the behavior of users and the way search engines rank pages, which are topics related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) and machine learning (cs.DL). Finally, the paper proposes a model that accurately predicts traffic data patterns, which is a topic related to social informatics (cs.SI).
